narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: This was a very conceptual class for AI, and we learn alot about the different views philosphers and scientists have on whether or not AI will ever be able to have a mind of its own

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: There was a small workload which was nice because it allowed stress free conversation during class discussions, and not many readings either

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. I learned a lot in this course, and it was engaging. The professor was interesting and cared a lot about our learning. He is also a very kind person.

The professor loves discussions, so that is what mainly goes on in class. The workload is very light, but the professor is a very hard grader which is good because it makes you a better writer by the end, but you have to really try when you do get assignments.
